I added the `NotNullWhen(returnValue: true)` attribute to an `out` string parameter in a method that returns a boolean.

If the very last return consists of `!string.IsNullOrEmpty(s)`, CS8762 gets unexpectedly triggered with this message:

> CS8762: Parameter '<paramName>' must have a non-null value when exiting with 'true'

Example:
```cs
using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;
public class C
{
    public bool TryMethod(
        int x,
        [NotNullWhen(returnValue: true)] out string s)
    {
        s = null;       
        if (x > 0)
        {
            s = x.ToString();
        }      
        return !string.IsNullOrEmpty(s);
    }
}
```
